modules.description: This module implements the OCRA (OATH Challenge-Response Algorithm) as defined by RFC 6287, providing functions to generate and verify cryptographic responses based on a shared key and challenge data. It supports operations for parsing OCRA suite strings, generating challenge strings, and computing or validating OCRA responses with configurable parameters such as PIN, timestamp, and counter values. The module works with data types including OCRA suite specifications, challenge strings, cryptographic digests, and timestamp values, targeting use cases like two-factor authentication and secure challenge-response protocols.
